<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="969" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d969">
                    <head>Teachers of the District of Nidau</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nidau</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">To the Editor of the Bund, in Berne:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>The teachers in the district of Nidau, in the canton of Berne, hereby declare
                        their cordial approval of the vote of sympathy and condolence to the United
                        States of North America, and beg that their names be added to the address of
                        the Swiss Confederation.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <salute>In the name of the synod of Nidau:</salute>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>D. SCHMUTZ, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                                <item>J. A. KAUFMANN, <hi rend="italic">Secretary</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>